		<span class="entitle">Risk of misinterpreting the Tea Bag Index: Field observations and a random simulation</span>
		<span class="authors">Taiki Mori, Ryosuke Nakamura and Ryota Aoyagi<br></span>
		<a href="https://doi.org/10.1111/1440-1703.12304" class="articlelink">https://doi.org/10.1111/1440-1703.12304</a>
	<div class="EICcomment"><strong>(編集長コメント)</strong> ティーバッグを利用してリターの分解速度を測定し比較する手法を利用する際に考慮すべき点を明らかにした研究です。このティーバッグを試料とする手法は、世界各地で用いられている手法であり、本研究の波及効果は極めて大きいです。また、シミュレーションを併用し野外調査で得られた指標の評価をする本研究の手法自体も応用範囲が広く、その点でも参考になる論文です。<br>
<strong>(副編集長コメント)</strong> ティーバッグを標準試料としたリター分解速度の評価法で生じうるバイアスについて指摘されています。<br>
		<br>
<strong>(Comment by Editor-in-Chief)</strong> This research clarified the points to be considered when using methods to measure and compare the decomposition rate of litter using the Tea Bag Index. The method using the Tea Bag Index as samples is a method used all over the world, and the ripple effect of this research is extremely high. In addition, the method in this research which evaluates the indicators obtained in the field survey by using simulations has a wide range of applications. This is a useful paper.<br>
<strong>(Comment by Deputy Editor-in-Chief)</strong> It points out to the bias that can occur in the evaluation method of litter decomposition rate when using the Tea Bag Index as a standard sample.<br>
					</div></li>
	
				<li><span class="category">ORIGINAL ARTICLES</span><span class="oa"></span><br>
